info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 24 at 1:27AM MST until February 25 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 11 PM THIS EVENING TO 11 PM MST SATURDAY... * WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 65 mph expected. Blowing snow may create visibility reductions below 1 mile at times. * WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County. * WHEN...From 11 PM this evening to 11 PM MST Saturday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 MPH or gusts of 58 MPH or more can lead to property damage.
